            <V n="text" t="variation">
              <U n="variation">
                <L n="variations">
                  <T>0x9CBF771C<!--A while back, I was walking around Crow's Crossing when I stumbled upon this strange book on a pedestal. I took a closer look and found my first <b>Tarot Card</b>! I've been working at understanding my tarot cards and have even started giving readings at the Thinned Festiveil. I have a bit of a family relation to a kinda famous local ghost who's connected to those tomes and the cards themselves. Seriously!--></T>
                  <T>0x67C1932<!--Not too long ago, I'm out with my mom and we run into Layne. He and mom get to talking, and she mentions this whole thing she's got about writing a Book of Life to get her sibling back. Layne gave her this weird grimace and just said, "Why would you spend your time on <i>that</i>?". Way out of character for him. He's usually supportive of uh, other creative people I guess, but he seemed so put off by my mom even mentioning a Book of Life.--></T>
                </L>
